                <h1>Understanding Android's Background Process Limits</h1>
                <p>On Android, background processes are limited to optimize performance and battery life. Each app can run a set number of background services simultaneouslyâ€”typically about 5. When this limit is reached, older processes may be killed to make room for new ones, balancing resource usage and ensuring smooth operation.</p>
